reviews.text: This station is busier than the towns second station, Wivelsfield, with around 12 trains an hour. This station is also served by Gatwick Express services, has disabled access to both platforms, waiting shelters on the north of both platforms, a small cafe on the northbound platform, a manned office at the top of the station and ticket barriers on every entrance and exit. Exit here and walk a couple minutes to reach the town centre

Sorry but this station is just not worth it. First of all the place is tiny and it is not fit within a big town. Second of all the gate's are really falty and doesnt work most of the time. There are not many staff there and as someone else said, the cutomar service is never open. Really dissapointed!
Ticket machines always breaking down, and the ticket office is hardly ever open. Gateline staff seem friendly enough, but the ticket office staff could do with some customer service training.
